{"id":739220,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Larry_Tesler","text":"Lawrence Gordon Tesler (April 24, 1945 \u2013 February 16, 2020) was an American computer scientist. He worked in the field of human\u2013computer interaction. He had worked at Xerox PARC, Apple, Amazon and Yahoo!.\nWhile at PARC, Tesler's work included Smalltalk, the first dynamic object-oriented programming language and Gypsy, the first word processor with a graphical user interface for the Xerox Alto. He also helped create the idea of copy and paste and the idea of modeless software.\nTesler was born in the the Bronx, New York. He died on February 16, 2020 in Portola Valley, California of problems caused from a bike accident. He was 74.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Americans","surface_form":"American","offset":67},{"uri":"Computer_scientist","surface_form":"computer scientist","offset":76},{"uri":"Human%E2%80%93computer_interaction","surface_form":"human\u2013computer interaction","offset":122},{"uri":"Xerox_PARC","surface_form":"Xerox PARC","offset":167},{"uri":"Apple_Inc.","surface_form":"Apple","offset":179},{"uri":"Amazon.com","surface_form":"Amazon","offset":186},{"uri":"Yahoo%21","surface_form":"Yahoo!","offset":197},{"uri":"Smalltalk","surface_form":"Smalltalk","offset":243},{"uri":"Dynamic_programming","surface_form":"dynamic","offset":264},{"uri":"Object-oriented_programming","surface_form":"object-oriented programming language","offset":272},{"uri":"Gypsy_(software)","surface_form":"Gypsy","offset":313},{"uri":"Word_processor","surface_form":"word processor","offset":330},{"uri":"Graphical_user_interface","surface_form":"graphical user interface","offset":352},{"uri":"Xerox_Alto","surface_form":"Xerox Alto","offset":385},{"uri":"Cut%2C_copy%2C_and_paste","surface_form":"copy and paste","offset":431},{"uri":"Mode_(user_interface)","surface_form":"modeless","offset":462},{"uri":"The_Bronx","surface_form":"the Bronx","offset":504},{"uri":"New_York_(state)",